entries.femaleVariant: Hello, Night City. This is Gillean Jordan with an N54 News campaign update. Exit polls have finally been tallied.

Incumbent Weldon Holt of the Devolutionist Party received a paltry 27.2 percent of the vote. His campaign floundered following charges filed against him in a murder investigation of Lucius Rhyne, former mayor of Night City.
Federalist candidate Jefferson Peralez won a resounding victory with 70.7 percent of the vote.
In his concession speech, Mayor Holt offered his congratulations to the victor.
Now we see whether Peralez will be able to realize his ambitious campaign promises.
